sentences: In 1933, Cavallaro joined Al Kavelin's orchestra, where he quickly became the featured soloist.
After four years, he switched to a series of other big bands, including Rudy Vallee's in 1937.
Cavallaro formed his own band, a five-piece combo, in St. Louis, Missouri, in 1939.
Cavallaro became a member of ASCAP in 1957.

Cavallaro also became famous through the media of radio and film, firstly with his regular program on NBC during the 1940s, The Sheaffer Parade, of which he was the host, and later in films where he played himself, starting with Hollywood Canteen (1944), then Diamond Horseshoe, Out of This World (both 1945) and The Time, The Place and The Girl (1946).

His most celebrated film achievement was playing the piano music for actor Tyrone Power’s hands to mime, in The Eddy Duchin Story (1956).
Cavallaro was married to Wanda Cavallaro on 6 May 1935.
They were divorced on 28 December 1962.
Cavallaro died from prostate cancer on 12 October 1989 in Columbus, Ohio.
